author: Daniel Gallen
title: Kickoff set for Maryland-Iowa
text:
Kickoff set for Maryland-Iowa Loh on University of Maryland football coach situation 
In a meeting with The Baltimore Sun editorial board, University of Maryland, College Park President Wallace Loh talks about the firing of Randy Edsall and what the university will be looking for in a new football coach. (Kevin Richardson/Baltimore Sun) 
In a meeting with The Baltimore Sun editorial board, University of Maryland, College Park President Wallace Loh talks about the firing of Randy Edsall and what the university will be looking for in a new football coach. (Kevin Richardson/Baltimore Sun) Daniel Gallen Contact Reporter Kickoff set for Maryland-Iowa on Halloween. 
The Maryland-Iowa matchup on Oct. 31 will kick off at 3:30 p.m. and will be televised on ABC locally, Iowa announced Monday . 
The game will be Maryland's only one of the season played in the Central time zone and is the second of three straight 3:30 p.m. Eastern kickoffs. The matchup will kick off at 2:30 p.m. Central. The Terps lost their only game played in the Central time zone last season, a 52-7 defeat at Wisconsin. 
Maryland takes on Penn State this weekend at M&T Bank Stadium in Baltimore. That game kicks off at 3:30 p.m. Maryland faces Wisconsin at home on Nov. 7, and that will also kick off at 3:30.
